The method should do the following:

> Sets the value of a cue-instance variable based on its friendly name.

The current implementation does something else:

```
        public void SetVariable (string name, float value)
        {
            if (name == "Volume")
            {
                _volume = value;
                if (_curSound != null)
                    _curSound.SetCueVolume(_volume);
            }
            else
            {
                _engine.SetGlobalVariable (name, value);
            }
        }
```

This needs to be changed to a per instance list of variables that are used with the XAct presets when playing the sound. 

I'm not sure where the "Volume" variable name comes from - as far as I know there is not default variable to adjust the volume. 

I'll have a deeper look at this and try to implement it correctly. I couldn't find any other matching issue or pull request - has someone already been working on this?
